CatDescriptText: Mrs. Mary Harris, 2420 Waring St. was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, March 29, 1958, pg. 2 with question: "Do people, whom you know, place more emphasis on social life than civic responsibilities?" answer reads: "I think that it's about even. I, myself, do a lot of church work."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Mary Harris wearing dark horizontal pinstriped coat with wide lapels, holding paper bag, standing in front of window and brick wall with thermometer and advertising slogan
